Knitting pattern
(fig. 391).       The patterns
shown in figs.
391 and 392,
are more particularly
useful
for comforters,
shawls, hoods
and the like. The
needles, which
may be either of
bone or steel
must match the
cotton in size;
steel needles are
the best for any
thing finer than
No. 16, of D.M.C
Coton          tricoter.



